Package pl.put.poznan.transformer.logic.jsonParser

Class JsonParserFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.put.poznan.transformer.logic.jsonParser.JsonParserFactory
  • public class JsonParserFactory
extends Object
    Factory class for creating JSON parser instances with different configurations. Supports creation of basic parsers and decorated parsers with various functionalities.

      • getParser

        public static JsonParser getParser​(String jsonRaw,
                                   Boolean pretty,
                                   DecoratorType decoratorType,
                                   String[] keys)
        Creates a decorated JSON parser instance with a single decorator.
        Parameters:
        jsonRaw - The raw JSON string to be parsed
        pretty - Boolean flag indicating whether to prettify (true) or minify (false) the output
        decoratorType - The type of decorator to apply (PRUNE or QUERY)
        keys - Array of keys to be used by the decorator
        Returns:
        A decorated JsonParser instance

      • getParser

        public static JsonParser getParser​(String jsonRaw,
                                   Boolean pretty,
                                   DecoratorType[] decoratorTypes,
                                   String[][] keysArray)
        Creates a JSON parser instance with multiple decorators chained together.
        Parameters:
        jsonRaw - The raw JSON string to be parsed
        pretty - Boolean flag indicating whether to prettify (true) or minify (false) the output
        decoratorTypes - Array of decorator types to be applied in sequence
        keysArray - Array of key arrays, each corresponding to a decorator
        Returns:
        A JsonParser instance with chained decorators
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the number of decorators doesn't match the number of key arrays
